data.text:
This article is more than 12 years old

The former Met commissioner met ex-News of the World deputy editor Neil Wallis eight times between 2006 and 2010, it was revealed at the Leveson inquiry today. Wallis was arrested on suspicion of involvement in phone hacking on 14 July 2011. Stephenson resigned on 17 July 2011
